ANNA V. NAGENGAST, PROSECUTOR, v. BOARD OF EDUCATION OF THE CITY OF BAYONNE, DEFENDANT. Argued January term, 1928 Decided July 2, 1928.

Before Justices Parker, Minturn and Campbell.

For the prosecutor, Brenner & Kresch. For the defendant, Benny & Cruden. Per Curiam.

Eor the reason stated in the opinion filed in number 295, this term, involving substantially the same question, the writ in this ease will be dismissed.
